wCellFormattingEventArgs.FormattingApplied%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property, the display properties of the object returned by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewCellFormattingEventArgs.CellStyle%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property are used to render the cell.  \\n  \\n For more information about custom formatting using the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridView.CellFormatting> event, see [How to: Customize Data Formatting in the Windows Forms DataGridView Control](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).  \\n  \\n To avoid performance penalties when handling this event, access the cell through the parameters of the event handler rather than accessing the cell directly.  \\n  \\n To customize the conversion of a formatted, user-specified value into an actual cell value, handle the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridView.CellParsing> event.  \\n  \\n For more information about handling events, see [NIB: Consuming Events](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/01e4f1bc-e55e-413f-98c7-6588493e5f67).\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following code example demonstrates how to handle <xref:System.Windows.Forms.DataGridView.CellFormatting>.  \\n  \\n [!code-vb[System.Windows.Forms.GridViewUnbound#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.windows.forms.d_93_1.vb)]\\n [!code-cpp[System.Windows.Forms.GridViewUnbound#1](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/t-system.windows.forms.d_93_1.cpp)]\\n [!code-cs[System.Windows.Forms.GridViewUnbound#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.windows.forms.d_93_1.cs)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: 'public class DataGridViewCellFormattingEventArgs : System.Windows.Forms.ConvertEventArgs'\n  inheritance:\n  - System.EventArgs\n  - System.Windows.Forms.ConvertEventArgs\n  implements: []\n  inheritedMembers:\n  - System.Windows.Forms.ConvertEventArgs.DesiredType\n  - System.Windows.Forms.ConvertEventArgs.Value\n  platform:\n  - net462\n- uid: System.Windows.Forms.DataGridViewCellFormattingEventArgs.#ctor(System.Int32,System.Int32,System.Object,System.Type,System.Wi